06/06/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- BiH Security Minister Barisa Colak and Slovak Interior Minister Martin Pado sealed an agreement Monday (5 June) on co-operation between police services, as well as an accord on co-operation in fighting terrorism and organised crime.
They also signed an agreement on the readmission of persons that do not meet legal requirements for entry in the two countries.
Pado communicated Slovakia's readiness to share its experience with the EU integration process.
(FENA, PBS - 05/06/06)
